raritan.name: raritan

revisions.description: The following changes were made. 1) Added agentInetPortNumber under trapInformation 2) Added agentInetPortNumber as a varbind to all traps

The following changes were made. 1) added assetStripCascadePosition to the assetManagement table 2) added rackUnitRelativePosition to the assetManagement table. 3) added assetStripNumberOfRackUnits to the assetManagement table. 4) added assetStripType, assetStripCascadePosition, rackUnitRelativePosition, assetStripNumberOfRackUnits to the following traps. assetTagConnected assetTagDisconnected bladeExtensionConnected bladeExtensionDisconnected

The following changes were made. 1) added bladeTagID to assetTagConnected and assetTagDisconnected traps 2) added rackUnitCount to the following traps. assetTagConnected assetTagDisconnected bladeExtensionConnected bladeExtensionDisconnected assetStripStateChange
The following changes were made. 1) add logParentBladeID to AssetManagementLogEntryStruct
The following changes were made. 1) clarify documentation of LED operation mode: setting ledMode, ledColor or ledColorStr automatically switches the ledOperationMode to manual.
The following changes were made. 1) add logAssetStripState and extend logEventType with assetStripStateChange

The following changes were made. 1) clarify documentation regarding logSlotNumber: it is 0 a) indicating a tag on the main strip b) in case no strip is connected or the value is not valid for a certain log entry
The following changes were made. 1) added bladeExtensionSize to bladeExtensionConnected and bladeExtensionDisconnected traps
The following changes were made. 1) added logSize, oldestLogID, newestLogID and logEventCount 2) added assetManagementLogTable and assetManagementLogEntry

1) Added assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnected, assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnectedStr, assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnected, assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr to AssetStripConfigurationEntryStruct 2) Deprecated defaultLEDColorConnected, defaultLEDColorConnectedStr, defaultLEDColorDisconnected, defaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr

1) add rackUnitPosition to the following traps: assetTagConnected, assetTagDisconnected, bladeExtensionConnected, bladeExtensionDisconnected, rackUnitConfigurationChanged 2) rackUnitNumber in the traps now always corresponds with rackUnitID, clarify documentation accordingly
1) extended AssetStripConfigurationEntryStruct by assetStripType and numberOfComponentAssetStrips 2) added compositeAssetStripCompositionChanged trap
1) removed bladeSlotNumberingMode from AssetManagementEntryStruct 2) removed BladeSlotNumberingModeEnumeration 3) removed bladeSlotNumberingMode from the rackUnitConfigurationChanged trap
The following changes were made. 1) allow 0 in rackUnitPosition in case there is no strip connected 2) added none (nothing connected) and unknown (strip disconnected) to rackUnitType
The following changes were made. 1) allow a 0 in bladeExtensionSize in case there is no blade extension connected or the asset strip is disconnected.

The following changes were made. 1) added sysContact,sysName, sysLocation to all traps 2) added currentMainTagCount, currentBladeTagCount 3) added maxMainTagCount, maxBladeTagCount 4) added bladeExtensionOverflow 5) added traps bladeExtensionOverflowOccured, bladeExtensionOverflowCleared
The following changes were made. 1) Added assetStripName to all traps
1) added rackUnitName

1) added bladeExtensionConnected, bladeExtensionDisconnected traps 2) in AssetManagementEntryStruct renamed rackUnitSize to bladeExtensionSize 3) added bladeSlotPosition to BladeExtensionEntryStruct 4) added bladeSlotNumberingMode to AssetManagementEntryStruct 5) added BladeSlotNumberingModeEnumeration 6) added bladeSlotNumberingMode to the rackUnitConfigurationChanged trap

Support blade server extension segments: 1) added rackUnitType, rackUnitSize 2) added bladeExtensionTable and bladeExtensionEntry 3) added slotNumber to assetTagConnected and assetTagDisconnected traps
The following changes were made. 1) Modified blinking speeds in AssetManagementLEDModeEnumeration to fastBlink, slowBlink

The following changes were made. 1) Added ledOperationMode to the Tag Connected and Tag Disconnected Traps. 2) Modified the DESCRIPTION of rackUnitNumberingOffset. 3) Modified blinking speeds in AssetManagementLEDModeEnumeration to blinkFastest, blink2ndFastest

The following changes were made. 1) Added DeviceConfigurationParameterEnumeration, RackUnitNumberingModeEnumeration, AssetStripOrientationEnumeration 2) Added deviceConfigurationChanged Trap 3) Added deviceUserName, deviceChangedParameter, changedParameterNewValue to trapInformationGroup 4) Added blinking2(4) to AssetManagementLEDModeEnumeration 5) Add led mode and led color information to the Tag Connected and Tag Disconnected Traps. 6) Added rackUnitNumberingMode, rackUnitNumberingOffset, assetStripOrientation to AssetStripConfigurationEntryStruct 7) Added rackUnitPosition to AssetManagementEntryStruct 8) Added rackUnitConfigurationChanged Trap
The first version of the MIB.

raritan.contactinfo: Author: Raritan Americas, Inc. postal: Raritan Americas, Inc. 400 Cottontail Lane Somerset, NJ 08873 email: tech@raritan.com phone: +1 732 764 8886
raritan.description: This MIB describes the SNMP functions of the asset management capable products from Raritan Computer.

complianceRev1.name: complianceRev1
complianceRev1.description: The requirements for conformance to the ASSETMANAGEMENT-MIB. This is deprecated in favor of complianceRev2

complianceRev2.name: complianceRev2
complianceRev2.description: The requirements for conformance to the ASSETMANAGEMENT-MIB.

configGroup.name: configGroup
configGroup.description: A collection of objects representing configuration data.

configGroup2.name: configGroup2
configGroup2.description: A collection of objects representing configuration data.

assetManagementGroup.name: assetManagementGroup
assetManagementGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the ability to control the asset management strip.

trapInformationGroup.name: trapInformationGroup
trapInformationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information in the traps.

logGroup.name: logGroup
logGroup.description: A collection of objects representing log data.

AssetManagementLEDModeEnumeration.name: AssetManagementLEDModeEnumeration
AssetManagementLEDModeEnumeration.description: The mode of an LED for the asset manager.

AssetManagementLEDOperationModeEnumerati.name: AssetManagementLEDOperationModeEnumeration
AssetManagementLEDOperationModeEnumerati.description: The operation mode of an LED for the asset manager.

AssetStripStateEnumeration.name: AssetStripStateEnumeration
AssetStripStateEnumeration.description: The state of an asset strip.

AssetStripFirmwareUpdateStateEnumeration.name: AssetStripFirmwareUpdateStateEnumeration
AssetStripFirmwareUpdateStateEnumeration.description: The state of an asset strip firmware update.

LogEventTypeEnumeration.name: LogEventTypeEnumeration
LogEventTypeEnumeration.description: The type of a log event.

assetStripCount.name: assetStripCount
assetStripCount.description: The number of asset management strip units supported.

defaultLEDColorConnected.name: defaultLEDColorConnected
defaultLEDColorConnected.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when a tag is connected during automatic operation; in binary format. This is deprecated in favor of assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnected For SET operations, the value will be applied to all asset strips For GET operations, the value returned will be the value corresponding to asset strip 1

defaultLEDColorConnectedStr.name: defaultLEDColorConnectedStr
defaultLEDColorConnectedStr.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when a tag is connected during automatic operation; string with 3 hex octets This is deprecated in favor of assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnectedStr For SET operations, the value will be applied to all asset strips For GET operations, the value returned will be the value corresponding to asset strip 1

defaultLEDColorDisconnected.name: defaultLEDColorDisconnected
defaultLEDColorDisconnected.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when no tag is connected during automatic operation; in binary format. This is deprecated in favor of assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisConnected For SET operations, the value will be applied to all asset strips For GET operations, the value returned will be the value corresponding to asset strip 1

defaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr.name: defaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr
defaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when no tag is connected during automatic operation; string with 3 hex octets This is deprecated in favor of assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr For SET operations, the value will be applied to all asset strips For GET operations, the value returned will be the value corresponding to asset strip 1

assetStripConfigurationTable.name: assetStripConfigurationTable
assetStripConfigurationTable.description: A list of configuration entries. The number of entries is given by the value of assetStripCount.

assetStripConfigurationEntry.name: assetStripConfigurationEntry
assetStripConfigurationEntry.description: An entry containing configuration objects for a particular asset management strip unit.

assetStripID.name: assetStripID
assetStripID.description: A unique value for each asset strip. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of assetStripCount.

rackUnitCount.name: rackUnitCount
rackUnitCount.description: The number of rack-units for the asset management.

rackUnitNumberingMode.name: rackUnitNumberingMode
rackUnitNumberingMode.description: The rack unit nmbering mode for this asset strip.

rackUnitNumberingOffset.name: rackUnitNumberingOffset
rackUnitNumberingOffset.description: The offset (starting value) for rack Unit Numbering; This takes care of the case in which the asset strip is monitoring not all the assets but a subset of it, starting from racknumberingOffset. For example, the asset strip may be monitoring assets from 10 through 26; default value is 1

assetStripOrientation.name: assetStripOrientation
assetStripOrientation.description: Is the asset strip oriented such that the connector is at the top or the bottom? If the asset strip has a tilt sensor, then this varaible is read-only and an to set(write) it will result in an error. If the asset strip does not have a tilt sensor, then this variable is read-write

currentMainTagCount.name: currentMainTagCount
currentMainTagCount.description: Number of tags currently connected to the main strip.

currentBladeTagCount.name: currentBladeTagCount
currentBladeTagCount.description: Number of tags currently connected to blade extensions. This may be larger than the maxBladeTagCount. In this case an overflow occured and all tags over maxBladeTagCount are not recognized.

maxMainTagCount.name: maxMainTagCount
maxMainTagCount.description: Maximum number of tags on the main asset strip.

maxBladeTagCount.name: maxBladeTagCount
maxBladeTagCount.description: Maximum number of blade tags supported.

bladeExtensionOverflow.name: bladeExtensionOverflow
bladeExtensionOverflow.description: Set if the maximum number of supported tags on blade extensions is reached. When this flag is set, new tags on blade extensions won't be discovered anymore until other tags on blade extensions are removed.

numberOfComponentAssetStrips.name: numberOfComponentAssetStrips
numberOfComponentAssetStrips.description: The number of components building a composite asset strip.

assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnected.name: assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnected
assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnected.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when a tag is connected during automatic operation; in binary format.

assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnectedStr.name: assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnectedStr
assetStripDefaultLEDColorConnectedStr.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when a tag is connected during automatic operation; string with 3 hex octets

assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnected.name: assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnected
assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnected.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when no tag is connected during automatic operation; in binary format.

assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr.name: assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr
assetStripDefaultLEDColorDisconnectedStr.description: Default color of all LEDs (RGB) when no tag is connected during automatic operation; string with 3 hex octets

assetManagementTable.name: assetManagementTable
assetManagementTable.description: A list of asset management extries containing tag information and LED state. The number of entries is given by the value of rackUnitCount.

assetManagementEntry.name: assetManagementEntry
assetManagementEntry.description: An entry containing tag information and LED state for a rack unit.

rackUnitID.name: rackUnitID
rackUnitID.description: A unique value for each rack unit. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of rackUnitCount.

ledOperationMode.name: ledOperationMode
ledOperationMode.description: Operation mode of the LED (manual or automatic, based on tag connection).

ledMode.name: ledMode
ledMode.description: Mode of the LED (on, off, fastBlink,slowBlink). Setting this value automatically switches the ledOperationMode to manual.

ledColor.name: ledColor
ledColor.description: Color of the LED (RGB) in binary format. Setting this value automatically switches the ledOperationMode to manual.

ledColorStr.name: ledColorStr
ledColorStr.description: Color of the LED (RGB) in string format. It contains 3 hex octets for the RGB colors. Setting this value automatically switches the ledOperationMode to manual.

tagID.name: tagID
tagID.description: Asset management tag attached to the rack unit. Empty in case there is no tag attached.

tagFamily.name: tagFamily
tagFamily.description: Family of the asset management tag attached to the rack unit. Empty in case there is no tag attached.

rackUnitPosition.name: rackUnitPosition
rackUnitPosition.description: A number associated with each rack unit. Its value depends on the rack unit numbering mode. It ranges between 1 and the value of rackUnitCount. If the asset strip is disconnected, then the value is 0.

rackUnitType.name: rackUnitType
rackUnitType.description: Type of the connected tag (single server or blade extension). If the asset strip is disconnected, then the value is unknown. If the asset tag is disconnected, then the value is none.

bladeExtensionSize.name: bladeExtensionSize
bladeExtensionSize.description: In case a blade extension is connected this returns the number of slots on the extension. If the asset strip is disconnected or no blade is connected, then the value is 0.

rackUnitName.name: rackUnitName
rackUnitName.description: Name for a specific rackunit, may be feeely chosen.

assetStripCascadePosition.name: assetStripCascadePosition
assetStripCascadePosition.description: This is the position of the asset Strip in a cascaded chain. Numbered in ascending order starting with the asset strip connected to the device (EMX/PX). For non-cascaded asset strips, value = 1

rackUnitRelativePosition.name: rackUnitRelativePosition
rackUnitRelativePosition.description: This is the relative position of the rackUnit within the assetStrip. For cascaded asset strips such as the AMS-M2-Z and AMS-M3-Z, it is numbered in ascending order starting with the rackunit closest to the asset strip edge with the connector. For non-cascaded asset strips, value = 1

assetStripNumberOfRackUnits.name: assetStripNumberOfRackUnits
assetStripNumberOfRackUnits.description: For non-cascaded asset strips, value = rackUnitCount For cascaded asset strips, it is the number of rack units in the asset Strip. Examples: 2 forAMS-M2-Z, 3 for AMS-M3-Z.

bladeExtensionTable.name: bladeExtensionTable
bladeExtensionTable.description: A list of blade server extension entries containing tag information.

bladeExtensionEntry.name: bladeExtensionEntry
bladeExtensionEntry.description: An entry containing tag information for a blade server extension.

bladeSlotID.name: bladeSlotID
bladeSlotID.description: A unique value for each slot on a blade extension.

bladeTagID.name: bladeTagID
bladeTagID.description: Asset management tag attached to a blade extension at the rack unit. Empty in case there is no tag attached.

bladeSlotPosition.name: bladeSlotPosition
bladeSlotPosition.description: A number associated with each blade slot. It ranges between 1 and the value of bladeExtensionSize.

logSize.name: logSize
logSize.description: The number of entries in the asset management log table.

oldestLogID.name: oldestLogID
oldestLogID.description: The index of the oldest entry in the log table.

newestLogID.name: newestLogID
newestLogID.description: The index of the newest entry in the log table.

logEventCount.name: logEventCount
logEventCount.description: The total number of logged events.

assetManagementLogTable.name: assetManagementLogTable
assetManagementLogTable.description: A ring buffer containing asset management events.

assetManagementLogEntry.name: assetManagementLogEntry
assetManagementLogEntry.description: An entry in the asset management log table.

logIndex.name: logIndex
logIndex.description: The index of an entry in the log ring buffer. Its value ranges between 1 and logSize.

logTimeStamp.name: logTimeStamp
logTimeStamp.description: The time of the log entry in seconds relative to January 1, 1970 00:00 UTC.

logEventType.name: logEventType
logEventType.description: The type of this log entry.

logAssetStripNumber.name: logAssetStripNumber
logAssetStripNumber.description: A unique value for each asset strip. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of assetStripCount.

logRackUnitNumber.name: logRackUnitNumber
logRackUnitNumber.description: A unique value for each rack unit. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of rackUnitCount. It corresponds with rackUnitID, the fixed ordinal index of each rack unit.

logRackUnitPosition.name: logRackUnitPosition
logRackUnitPosition.description: A number associated with each rack unit. Its value depends on the rack unit numbering mode. It ranges between 1 and the value of rackUnitCount. If the asset strip is disconnected, then the value is 0.

logSlotNumber.name: logSlotNumber
logSlotNumber.description: A unique value for each slot on a blade extension. Value of 0 indicates a tag on the main strip. If the asset strip is disconnected, the value is 0 as well. Use logEventType to distinguish the validity.

logTagID.name: logTagID
logTagID.description: Asset management tag attached to the rack unit. Empty in case there is no tag attached.

logParentBladeID.name: logParentBladeID
logParentBladeID.description: In case the tag is attached to a blade extension, this indicates the tagID of the extension. Empty in case there is no tag attached or the tag is attached on the main strip.

deviceName.name: deviceName
deviceName.description: The user-defined name for the Device.

deviceInetIPAddress.name: deviceInetIPAddress
deviceInetIPAddress.description: The current IP address. A value of 0.0.0.0 indicates an error or an unset option.

assetStripNumber.name: assetStripNumber
assetStripNumber.description: A unique value for each asset strip. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of assetStripCount.

rackUnitNumber.name: rackUnitNumber
rackUnitNumber.description: A unique value for each rack unit. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of rackUnitCount. It corresponds with rackUnitID, the fixed ordinal index of each rack unit.

assetStripFirmwareUpdateState.name: assetStripFirmwareUpdateState
assetStripFirmwareUpdateState.description: The new asset strip firmware update state.

deviceChangedParameter.name: deviceChangedParameter
deviceChangedParameter.description: Description of the parameter(s) that changed.

changedParameterNewValue.name: changedParameterNewValue
changedParameterNewValue.description: The new value of the changed parameter.

slotNumber.name: slotNumber
slotNumber.description: A unique value for each slot on a blade extension. Value of 0 indicates a tag on the main strip.

oldNumberOfComponentAssetStrips.name: oldNumberOfComponentAssetStrips
oldNumberOfComponentAssetStrips.description: The old number of components building a composite asset strip.

agentInetPortNumber.name: agentInetPortNumber
agentInetPortNumber.description: The UDP port number used for accessing the SNMP agent on the device. Examples: If the associated device MIB (PX2-MIB, EMD-MIB) has deviceCascadeType set to portForwarding, then master: 50500 slave 1:50501 slave 2: 50502 ...... If cascading mode is not portForwarding and default (Standard) ports are being used, then port: 161

assetTagConnected.name: assetTagConnected
assetTagConnected.description: The asset tag of a rack unit was connected. bladeTagID is empty if the asset tag is not on a blade extension.

assetTagDisconnected.name: assetTagDisconnected
assetTagDisconnected.description: The asset tag of a rack unit was disconnected. bladeTagID is empty if the asset tag is not on a blade extension.

assetStripStateChange.name: assetStripStateChange
assetStripStateChange.description: The asset strip unit changed its state.

assetStripFirmwareUpdate.name: assetStripFirmwareUpdate
assetStripFirmwareUpdate.description: Asset strip firmware update state change.

bladeExtensionConnected.name: bladeExtensionConnected
bladeExtensionConnected.description: A blade extension has been connected to the rackunit.

bladeExtensionDisconnected.name: bladeExtensionDisconnected
bladeExtensionDisconnected.description: A blade extension has been disconnected from the rackunit.

bladeExtensionOverflowOccured.name: bladeExtensionOverflowOccured
bladeExtensionOverflowOccured.description: Maximum number of supported tags on blade extension was reached. The asset strip won't detect any new tags on blade extensions until some are removed.

bladeExtensionOverflowCleared.name: bladeExtensionOverflowCleared
bladeExtensionOverflowCleared.description: Free space for new tags on blade extensions is available again.

compositeAssetStripCompositionChanged.name: compositeAssetStripCompositionChanged
compositeAssetStripCompositionChanged.description: The composition of an composite asset strip changed.
